<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><entry xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:planet="http://planet.intertwingly.net/"><id>http://polylogblog.wordpress.com/2012/10/27/umass-hiring-in-theory/</id><link href="https://polylogblog.wordpress.com/2012/10/27/umass-hiring-in-theory/" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><title>UMass hiring in theory!</title><summary>After a very successful hiring season last year, the department is now focusing on hiring in theory, NLP, robotics, and vision (that’s four separate searches rather than one extreme interdisciplinary position).  So please apply! The official ad is here and note that, unlike previous years, we’re able to hire in theory at either the assistant or […]<div class="commentbar"><p/></div></summary><content type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>After a <a href="https://www.cs.umass.edu/news/latest-news/department-welcomes-five-new-faculty">very successful hiring season</a> last year, the department is now focusing on hiring in theory, NLP, robotics, and vision (that’s four separate searches rather than one extreme interdisciplinary position).  So please apply! The official ad is <a href="https://www.cs.umass.edu/content/assistant-associate-professor-university-massachusetts-amherst-department-computer-science">here</a> and note that, unlike previous years, we’re able to hire in <a href="http://people.cs.umass.edu/~immerman/theoryOfComputation.html">theory</a> at either the assistant or associate level. We’ll start reviewing applications December 3.
</p>
